body:
I am currently writing a toree plugin that leverage the PySpark Interpreter to run the Pixiedust Python library auto-viz capability (https://github.com/ibm-cds-labs/pixiedust) from a Scala notebook. What's interesting about this feature is that it brings viz rendering using Matplotlib, seaborn, bokeh and others to scala users.

This PR is firing 2 events that are needed by my plugin (see comment above), with no side effect if no plugin is currently handling them.

@mariusvniekerk : Please let me know if you need me to create a JIRA for this PR.

Sure, why not. The plugin system was meant to accrue more event types to support varying cases. It seems like having a post run cell event to compliment the pre run cell event would make sense.

I'm starting to think we should have a common object to store the event names to make it less likely to mis-type the event. Something like...

```scala
object PluginEvents {
  /** Signalled when all interpreters have been initialized. */
  val AllInterpretersReady: String = "allInterpretersReady"

  /** Signalled before executing a block of code. */
  val PreRunCell: String = "preRunCell"

  /** Signalled after executing a block of code. */
  val PostRunCell: String = "postRunCell"
}
```

@chipsenkbeil This is such a long time ago. I think there are some changes here that should make it to both the 0.1.x and master branch. More specifically:

1. The changes to remove legal files from src distro 
2. The changes to rename the package to `apache-toree`
